• Pros and Cons of Waterfall - Model Development Strategy
    - Pros
      1. Easy to understand process.
      2. Easy to estimated deadline.
      3. There is no revise backward.
      4. Tear down project into a small piece and share each task to team member easily.
    - Cons
      1. If requirement changes, current process must be stopped and restart again.
      2. Schedule usually delayed than expected schedule.
      3. Not suitable with user that is not know about him/herself own requirement.
      4. Not suitable with huge size of project.
      5. Need a lot communication in team to set same understanding level.
• V-Model
  - It has two phases, One is verification phase and another one is validation phase, both phases are working in the same time.
    1. Verification Phase
       This phase is about define concept
